President Cyril Ramaphosa has noted the resignation of Jabu Mabuza as Eskom chairperson. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom board chairperson Jabu Mabuza has resigned. Mabuza used his resignation to apologise for Eskom's inability to meet power demand. READ: Cosatu says Eskom board must face consequences President Cyril Ramaphosa's office confirmed the resignation. Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan accepted the resignation. READ: The president was misled about load-shedding, says Mabuza Ramaphosa expressed gratitude to Mabuza for his service to the nation during a "challenging period". The president further commended Mabuza for taking responsibility and accepting accountability for the events that took place under his leadership. The Presidency stated they would soon announce a re-configured Eskom board.